    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Chicago is the third largest city in the United State and located next to the Great Lakes, which leaves  this metropolitan area with four distinct seasons.  Summers are hot and winters are cold, but there are full plenty of places to visit and things to do year round!  Known for its variety, there are lots of places to fill your stomach, including high class restaurants  and local food vendors, where you can sample food from all around the world.  For those who love to shop, there is the famous "Magnificent Mile", which has department stores like Saks Fifth Avenue and Nordstrom, jewelry stores, small galleries, boutiques, restaurants and food courts.  Looking to do more than shop and eat?  There's ice skating at the McCormick Tribune Ice Rink in Millennium Park, art exhibitions downtown, movies in a 3D IMAX theater with two large, educational museums and a 150 foot Ferris Wheel down at the Navy Pier, and running, walking, cycling or rollerblading at one of Chicago's 552 public parks that are open year round.  Home to seven professtional sports teams, such as the Cubs, White Sox, and Bulls, one can visit Wrigley Field, the oldest park in the Nation League, Soldier Field or the United Center, where a large statue of Michael Jordan is on display.  If you are still looking for more to do, an area known as the Theater District will certainly satisfy your craving.  There are five beautifully restored theaters, including world famous The Chicago Theater, open and running since 1921 and holding up 3,600 people at a time.  With an ambulance to do and keep one occupied, Chicago is a great city for anyone to enjoy!</p>
