    <h3>District Information</h3>
    <p>Chicago Public Schools is the third largest school in the United States, meaning a multitude of courses, sports, clubs and other activities are available.  With a goal to provide unique learning opportunities to its students inside and outside the classroom, new programs are looking to help those who are interested in moving up in their education.  Some of these programs include the Chicago Book Clubs, the Chicago Math and Science Initiative, and the Chicago Reading Initiative.  Many students also participate in The United States Academic Decathlon, which a national academic competition.  The Chicago Public Schools has the largest number of participants that enroll in this competition, more than any other school district in the country, and for the past 20 years has placed in the top five.  Striving to create an environment where every child in every high school can flourish and achieve their full potential is the goal of Chicago Public Schools</p>
